  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The model predicts absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. All 13 credibility factors are assessed; seven factors show achieved levels below required levels. Decision: Accepted with residual monitoring plan. Intended use is limited to pre-market submission support for rotodynamic blood pumps operating in VAD mode at 2500–3500 RPM, 4–6 L/min flow, with NIH as the primary quantity of interest.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-requirement",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/cfd-hemolysis-vad-absolute-prediction",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/cfd-hemolysis-giersiepen-wbk",
  "bindsDataset": [
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-piv-experimental",
    "https://uofa.net/synth/data/fda-pump-hemolysis-nih-measurements"
  ],
